programme.title: Live Nissan Super Sunday
programme.desc: Crystal Palace v Tottenham Hotspur (Kick-off 12.00pm). Coverage of the Premier League clash, which takes place at Selhurst Park. Roy Hodgson's Eagles lost their last league game against Everton 3-1 at Goodison Park, while Spurs beat fierce north London rivals Arsenal 1-0 at Wembley Stadium thanks to Harry Kane's second-half header. That result moved them seven points ahead of the Gunners in the table

programme.title: Live Nissan Super Sunday

programme.title: Live Carabao Cup
programme.sub-title: Live Carabao Cup Final: Arsenal v Manchester City.
programme.desc: Arsenal v Manchester City (Kick-off 4.30pm). All the action from the showpiece match at Wembley Stadium, as the sides battle it out for the trophy. While Arsenal have had success here in recent years, winning the FA Cup three times in the last four seasons, this competition has eluded them since 1993. In contrast, the Citizens have lifted this trophy in 2014 and 2016 and will start as slight favourites given their excellent form this term
